            "views": [
                { "type": "text", "text": "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The<\/span><strong> Hotel Boscolo Milano<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> nestled in the city of Milan (<\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Italy<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">) is the perfect blend of modernity and luxury. The hotel is bathed in natural light because of the massive windows facing the Corso Matteotti. The Boscolo Milano is perfectly situated for easy access to all the biggest and best events in the fields of finance, fashion, and design.<\/span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The interior design of the hotel<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is the crop of the visionary and talented architect Italo Rota, who has completely rethought the building on Corso Matteotti formerly housing IMI Bank. The shapes, solutions and colors are distinctly unique in the hotel world. The <\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">brave design<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> spends all over the ground floor, reception and bar area, restaurant, conference, iconic spa and roof garden. The design of the rooms, however, is not accommodated for a comfortable and relaxing stay. Vivid colours and confusing space distribution force the visitors to spend little time in the rooms regardless of the amazing city views and luxury interior.<\/span><\/p>" },
                { "type": "grid", "content": [
                    ["/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Plan01.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Plan02.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Desk Area.jpg"]
                ]},
                { "type": "text", "text": "<p><strong><em>De&rsquo;Light<\/em><\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a concept for a new master suite in Boscolo Milano. The primary design intent is to create a space where the flow between zones and activities comes naturally and privacy is attained by the nonstandard spatial distribution and partition. The goal is to develop a space where the visitor can experience a space with a clear distinction between &ldquo;<\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">calming<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&rdquo; and &ldquo;<\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">refreshing<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&rdquo; areas that are intertwined into a minimal and luxurious environment. The key design driver for the spatial distribution is immersive fluidity. The space is welcoming and immerses the guest into a premium environment that wants to be explored and experienced. <\/span><\/p>" },
                { "type": "grid", "content": [
                    ["/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Backlit Onyx.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Bad Back.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Closet Backlit.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Fragments.jpg"],
                    ["/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Closet Cove.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Devine Cove.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Bad Down.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Laser Blade.jpg"]
                ]},
                { "type": "text", "text": "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Custom light fixtures from &ldquo;<\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">divinity ceiling coves<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&rdquo; to &ldquo;<\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">energizing OLED fragments<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&rdquo; divide the range of spaces into two main categories based on activity and sentiment: <\/span><strong>calming <\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and <\/span><strong>refreshing<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Each light feature was specifically designed to create an <\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">illusion <\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">of illumination without an existing source. The backlit onyx panels, down-lit furniture elements, curvy ceiling profiles with spotlights are oriented to achieve maximum comfort and balance. The master suite is designed with few but exquisite materials such as oak wood, rose gold, marble and titanium coated plaster that changes according to the range of lighting scenarios provided by the custom-designed light fixtures. <\/span><strong><em>De&rsquo;Light<\/em><\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a concept for a space that adapts to the needs of the user dynamically and changes between lighting scenarios both manually and automatically. The space both guides you and is guided by you, providing a unique experience that would make anyone come back to Boscolo Milano.&nbsp; <\/span><\/p>" },
                { "type": "grid", "content": [
                    ["/dna/media/projects/delight/content/PlanView.jpg"],
                    ["/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Section FF.jpg"],
                    ["/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Section EE.jpg"],
                    ["/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Section GG_Lit Bar.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Section BB.jpg", "/dna/media/projects/delight/content/Section DD.jpg"]
                ]},
                { "type": "text", "text": "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This <\/span><strong>contrast <\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">of activities is reflected in the formal language of the space. The relaxing areas such as the lounge, bedroom, and bathtub area are <\/span><strong>curvy and fluid<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in shape with no sharp angles and hidden light elements. The boosting or energizing areas such as the entrance\/exit, desk, bar, and shower are all formally expressed with <\/span><strong>sharp angles<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and <\/span><strong>fragmented surfaces<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> with hidden back-lit panels that slowly activate as you spend more time in the area.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The space is organized so that as you enter there is no direct view to the bed, maximising guest <\/span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">privacy<\/span><\/em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Rather, upon entry you are faced with a choice: to go to the lounge and relax or to unpack in the premium open closet with plenty of space and range of custom features. As you start exploring the space, you will notice how seamless the <\/span><strong>light follows and guides<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> you to the marble bathroom with an oakwood hot tub with a view towards the city. The space also holds an unconventional shower with color therapy and massaging a horizontal bed that can take the stress away after a long day or gives you a morning energy boost. The master suite is perfectly accommodated for a mindful working session in the desk area where strong direct illumination emerges from the fragmented wall element.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The space was designed in September 2015 as a concept proposal for Hotel Boscolo Milano, Italy<\/span><\/em><\/p>\r\n" }
            ]
        },
